Rating: 0
I absolutely agree about making double this recipe. It's a great meal all on it's own for two, and you'll want more to freeze. I use olive oil instead of butter, or you could use half of each. I also saute the onions until they're caramelized, if I have time, though I like the suggestion to roast them in the oven along with the garlic. You can caramelize onions by slicing them about 1/4" thick, then treat them as I do the pre-peeled garlic: toss with olive oil, spread out in a thick layer on a foiled baking sheet(if they're spread too far apart they may brown too much), seal by covering with another layer of foil, and roast at 300F for about 30 min. As for the cream, I throw in a can of cannelini beans. It makes the soup creamy and hearty without the extra fat, and I personally think it goes better with the other flavors than cream. Lemon juice or a little white balsamic is excellent, but I do without the Parmesan (or just use a smattering of cheese to top) and it's excellent

