Like most cooks, I use a of garlic so whenever I sense that a bulb is going south I roast it. In my kitchen, roasted garlic finds its way into pizza sauces, quiches, and creamy sauces for chicken. So this soup is great when more than one bulb is starting to sprout. I love it and find new ways to change it up. To make it more of a meal, I've added sausage (casing removed before cooking with the onions and deglazing with white wine or sherry thereafter) or leftover chicken. To top it I've used leftover chopped tomatoes (heirlooms are so good with it!), chopped avocado. I've also thrown in leftover corn and/or beans. Soup - it's all about what you've got to use before it goes bad. Have fun with it!

