Rating: 4
Mmm...so comforting and delicious on a chilly, rainy evening. To make things easier, I use a jar of peeled cloves. While they're roasting in a pie pan, I put the sliced onions in a dutch oven with a knob of butter and put it in the oven with the garlic. Give them a stir now and them and they're about ready when the garlic is. Why stand and stir when the oven will do all the work? After simmering with the stock, I just whir my immersion blender around and it's done! I add just a splash of cream but, next time, I don't think I'll add any at all. It really is so creamy on its own. By the way, I made and ate this on a Thursday night because my Friday meeting was cancelled. When I found out it was back on, I was mortified. I'm sure the garlic smell was oozing right out of my pores! It's gotta be a weekend treat for me!

