Rating: 3
Really good, tasty, creamy soup made with a minimum of cream. The cheese and lemon really finish off the flavors. I took someone's suggestion and added wild mushroom tortellini to this just before serving, and, inspired to make this soup a meal on its own, added a bunch of pencil-thin asparagus, cut on the diagonal into 1.5" lengths and microwaved just till cooked. Actually, the asparagus was the biggest hit! I'd definitely make it again--it's quick, too, if you roast the garlic a day ahead.

